tches:\n            path = matches[0]\n    df = prepare_beach_datasheet(path)\n    failed = df[df['Enterococcus'] > 104]\n    rain_failed += int((failed['1-Day Rain'] > 0).sum())\n    total_failed += int(len(failed))\n\npercentage = (rain_failed / total_failed * 100) if total_failed else 0.0\nprint(f'{percentage:.2f}')\n", "reason": "Rewrote the solution to avoid the missing text file dependency and directly aggregate across all Boston Harbor beach datasheet CSVs. It robustly locates files in the sandbox, reshapes the two-row-header beach datasheets into tidy form, counts samples with Enterococcus > 104 and positive 1-Day Rain, computes the overall percentage, and prints it rounded to 2 decimals."}) [toolUseId=call_mqkeLHDdczpnPIunBirxTVLe]
