2026-05-17 05:13:26 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #6 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Compute percent of failed samples (Enterococcus <=104 to meet standard; fail if >104) with positive 1-Day Rain within 24h prior, across all Boston Harbor beach datasheets. Use all provided beach datasheet CSVs for Boston Harbor beaches.", "code": "import pandas as pd, numpy as np, re\n\npaths = {\n 'm_street': r'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"m_street\"]',\n 'constitution_8': r'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"constitution_8\"]',\n 'carson': r'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"carson\"]',\n 'pleasure': r'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"pleasure\"]',\n 'constitution_12': r'DOWNLOAD_PATHS[\"constitution_12\"]',\n}\n\ndef load(path):\n    df = pd.read_csv(path)\n    # first row/col structure: first 1-2 columns are labels; real columns: Date,1-Day Rain,2-Day Rain,3-Day Rain,Tag,Enterococcus,(Tag,Enterococcus)*\n    df.columns = [c.replace('\"','').strip() for c in df.columns]\n    # Identify Date column name containing 'Date'\n    date_col = None\n    for c in df.columns:\n        if 'Date' in c:\n            date_col = c\n            break\n    if date_col is None:\n        date_col = df.columns[0]\n    # Identify 1-Day Rain numeric col\n    rain1_col = None\n    for c in df.columns:\n        if '1-Day Rain' in c:\n            rain1_col = c\n            break\n    # Enterococcus count columns: those containing 'Enterococcus'\n    enter_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'Enterococcus' in c]\n    return df, date_col, rain1_col, enter_cols\n\nall_counts=[]\nfor key, path in paths.items():\n    df, date_col, rain1_col, enter_cols = load(path)\n    # Each beach datasheet may have multiple sites (e.g., constitution north/middle/south). We treat each Enterococcus column independently with its associated Tag column.\n    # Determine associated 1-day rain value is shared across row.\n    # For each Enterococcus column, parse values; failure if numeric >104 or if string begins with '>' maybe? The standard: sample meets standard if <=104 counts. So fail if >104.\n    # Dataset includes entries like '<,10' or '10'?? Let's inspect by parsing generic numeric from cell.\n    def cell_to_num(x):\n        if pd.isna(x):\n            return np.nan\n        s=str(x).strip()\n        # sometimes combined like '<' and value in separate columns? Actually Tag and Enterococcus separated.\n        # If cell is like '10' or '10.5' or '602'\n        # Extract first number\n        m=re.search(r'(-?\\d+\\.?\\d*)', s)\n        return float(m.group(1)) if m else np.nan\n\n    rain1 = df[rain1_col].apply(cell_to_num) if rain1_col else pd.Series([np.nan]*len(df))\n    for ec in enter_cols:\n        nums = df[ec].apply(cell_to_num)\n        mask = ~nums.isna()\n        failed = mask & (nums>104)\n        rainpos = (rain1>0)  # positive 1-day rain\n        num_failed = int(failed.sum())\n        num_failed_rainpos = int((failed & rainpos).sum())\n        all_counts.append((key, num_failed, num_failed_rainpos))\n\ntotal_failed = sum(x[1] for x in all_counts)\nnum_failed_rainpos = sum(x[2] for x in all_counts)\npercent = (num_failed_rainpos/total_failed*100) if total_failed else 0\nprint('counts_by_sheet', all_counts)\nprint('total_failed', total_failed)\nprint('failed_with_rainpos', num_failed_rainpos)\nprint('percent', round(percent,2))\n"}) [toolUseId=call_i2iwmdrKljEZdsTmMVkptBKl]
